subject: Re: Lexical sets and QS letters
msgSnippet: ... That s good to hear, thanks for the feedback. I m very glad we are already producing something useful.
messageBody:
--- In Read_Alphabet@yahoogroups.com, "Ted Larson Freeman"
<freeman@...> wrote:
>
> Anthony,
>
> Upon some reflection, you're right about SQUARE. After looking at the
> lexical sets again and thinking through my own pronunciation of each
> one, #28 is best for this set. I will now replace the #29+#25 ligature
> with #28+#25.
>
> Thanks again for the chart. What I've been lacking in my attempt to
> learn QS is examples to guide me. This lexical set exercise is exactly
> what I needed.
>
> Ted
>

That's good to hear, thanks for the feedback. I'm very glad we are
already producing something useful.
